Bring a large pot of water to boil and season with salt. Meanwhile in a nonstick skillet saute chicken thighs on both sides until brown; season with salt and pepper. Add rosemary and lemon zest. Saute for one more minute and stir in the sauce and 1 cup of water; bring to a simmer. Meanwhile cook pasta according to directions, drain and toss with sauce. Stir in cheese before serving.